review_blob: For a Heineken brew this one come out prety good.  Very nice deep color similar to Barqs Root Beer and has a minor bitter quality with a quite malty overtone.  This is probobly the best brew by Heineken.  Much better than their skunky green bottle beers.

beer_brewer_name: Vermont Hard Cider Company, LLC (C&C; Group)
review_blob: A palatable autumn drink, it is a bit sweet and taste best at colder temperatures.   It is a nice crisp tasting cider beer.  (Boarderlining to sweet)

Is this really a dark beer?  No.  This is very likable as a drinker.  This is not for the serious dark beer drinker...  right along the same line as St. Pauli Girl Dark.  It is a nice looking dark red.  Translucent not like the real dark beers. Has s good fall seasonal flavor.

This has a pleasing earthy tone...  It has avery natural aroma bleeding of coffee and almond?  I get a hint of almond out of this one...  The thick frothy head was also pleasant and reminded me of a dark creamy ale.  This is a near perfcect brew.
Smells and Looks quite nice.  It leans (IMO) closer to a Cream Ale mixed with and ESB. It is a bit malty in its aroma and fininshes like furnature polish.

Quite a HOPPY one...  it also has a quite an active yeast in its over tones... as well, and lasts in the after taste.  Not quite as good of a finish as Two Hearted Ale but not to bad.  It does have a citrus aroma but hardly notice it in the flavor...  I prefer the  finish of the KZoo IPA.
This was quite hoppy as mst IPAs but it was a bit over board.  The aroma was much better than the taste.
beer_name: Sailor Hagars Jewel in the Crown IPA

review_blob: I bought a 1994 case of this in 1997 and still have 10 bottles left.  This has almost a brandy affect.  This is not to be taken like a regular beer.  Best served at room temp in a sniff...  and this is a sipper not a drinker.  I like this one on a really cold night and by the fire.  As they continue to age they just get better.  A very good friend and myself have shared these over the last few x-mass (missed the last one)...  the older the better.  It continues to mature and get smoother.
Not bad for a cider/beer...  initial taste is a bit fruity sweet but after a few bottles it goes down quite nice and has a nice finish.  Good summer brew for hanging out by the pool.

I had to knock this one down a little on flavor, in my opinion there to many flavors going on in this one.  Yet it is very drinkable dont get me wrong, it has a black licorice (anise) flavor that is a bit strong to my liking.  My overall opinion on this is quite high...  about the best  Bells makes.

Simply Awesome.  The only downfall of this is the extreme unfiltered appearance.  It is extremely cloudy and near orange in color.  Its hoppy taste takes over your palate and has almost a fruity after taste.  Its fairly generic label might have you pass right by for something with a bt more attraction... well the atraction of this one is not what is on the outside of the bottle but whats on the inside!

This is my preferred beer for drinking...  This beer does not have the regular skunky taste found in several of the other Green bottled German Beers.  This is not the world best beer, but is very palatible.

This is probobly the best Mexican Beer you can get.  It is a really light straw color with a sweet aftertaste.  This one is worth a try...  I generally lean towards Tradidtional German Pils and this could easily fit into the pilsener class.  It is not as light and tasteless as most of the Mexican beer that conform to the American Standard.  I beleive this also falls under the German Purity Laws...
Prety average, nice color with a nice aftertaste.  This is a nice summer beer.
Reminds me very much of Bud, although its flavor is a little better.  Very similar to Tecate.
Chineese Light.  This has a nice aroma that comes off much stronger than its taste.  This is quite light and crisp.
This is quite average, I used to like it 10 years ago but as my tastes mature and the skunky aroma is a turn-off on this one.  This should be Extra Skunky Pilsener...
For and extra-special bitter it is not, this beer is more like a lager, sort of reminds me of Fosters with a slightly fuller body.
Red Stripe is an average beer, although it has a nice amber color and best when served extermely cold.
Nice.  This does not takelike a regular lager, it has more of the features of a pilsner.  I laos collect the bottles for my own brewing.

I like this lager.  This is a nice summer (warm weather) drinker.  Nice head, crisp and smooth.

This is the key ingredient if you like black and tans, the best is 50% Harp and 50% Guinness mixed in a tall pils glass.  Much better than the pre-mixed Black and Tans.
This has a skunky aftertaste like many of the green bottle German Beers.  The fresher the better as this one seems to get skunkier with any aging.
This is quite plesent, this is a nice mix of malty and hoppy after taste.  It almost has the quality of some of the mirobrews that have IPA qualities and active fermentation.
Even worse than its full flavored predisisor BUD.  These are aweful.
I do not know how this beer has made it so popular this beer is over carbonated with very little but bad flavor.  I think this beer only made it becase of its advertising.
This is a very good Japaneese beer, I prefer Kerin in this catergory.  This beer is best when from the Stainless Steel Can.  It seems to lose some of its color and body.
This is a very average beer.  If you like lighter beers this might be for you.
